latestIgtvVideos.title: Luxaderme Foot Peeling Masks
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Recently @luxaderme sent me amazing footmasks. 🌸🌸🌸
How you should use - Foot Peeling Masks?? 1)Cleanse your feet properly and remove the nailpaint. I didn't remove it and it is not the correct way to use it so be careful.
2)Remove the mask from the package, cut it from between and wear the socks.
3)You can keep the mask from 1-2 hours.
4)You can soak your feet in lukewarm water everyday for 5 min for better and faster results. (Do not use any scrub or try to peel off the skin forcibly during the peeling process.)
5)After 3-5 days the dead skin will gradually start to peel off and in about 10-12 days most if not all the dead, calloused, dirty skin will be removed (results may vary depending on skin type) and you have smooth baby soft skin naturally !!
.
The footmask is available in Nykaa.

latestPosts.caption:
"Aren't you bored staying all by yourself? Don't you wanna hangout and be around people? How do you manage to stay alone, you need someone always"- have heard these more than often from so many people!
As much as they are right in their perspectives, staying alone can come with a lot of pros and cons, pros more if you like yourself enough. 
As much as I miss my parents or my partner, I would not trade an alone time for anything else in this world!
Do I feel lonely? NO
Over the years I have managed to love myself enough to not get tired by my own company! 
 I know me and I can never get enough of me!
Does that mean I don't love or like anyone else?
Well, yes but they say "A man can only meet another person with the same depth they have met themselves ".
Some slow evenings make me grounded more than ever. 
And I acknowledge my privileges 🧿💞
If this song were a human 🥂

It is believed that a woman’s voice is louder when she’s silent. And dangerous when she speaks.

We talk about women’s safety like it's a concept. But the truth is—it isn’t unsafe for women just on roads at night. It’s unsafe for women even inside their phones, in their DMs, and in their comments section.

This isn't about just one creator. This is about all of us. And if this enrages you, good. It should.

We’re not raising our voices for attention. We’re raising them because silence gets women killed.
